# SQLite Dialect Changes

When you add, change, or remove SQLite-specific behavior (including workarounds, rebuild logic, dialect differences, or config flags tied to SQLite), **update** [docs/technical/04-sqlite-vs-postgres-differences.md](docs/technical/04-sqlite-vs-postgres-differences.md).

## When to update

- Modifying `src/dbconform/sql_dialect/sqlite*.py`, `sqlite_rebuild.py`
- Changing `allow_sqlite_table_rebuild`, `allow_shrink_column`, or other SQLite-related flags
- Adding or changing SQLite workarounds (e.g. index naming, CHECK rewriting, default translation)
- Discovering new SQLite vs PostgreSQL behavioral differences

## How to update

- Add or revise the relevant section in the document
- Keep the "Impact on dbconform" and "Mitigation" subsections accurate
- If you add a new difference, document it so future contributors can find it
